I get better breakfast burritos from the AAFES gas station in the hot box for the same price and don't need to wait 30 minutes when I was told 15.

text: Friendly employees and very clean station with a large selection of items including DEF for Diesel engines  Not sure why one reviewer said employees were rude. I am there regularly and have always received very friendly customer service. The high volume truck island diesel pumps are convenient for quick truck fill up. Easy access in and out and very good food. Chicken fingers are a favorite. Large quantities. Highly Recommended!

name: Trviestious Cole
text: Ms. Shannon that works there is amazing. I was out on a delivery and got very sick, I pulled over to the store and utilized the bathroom. Ms. Shannon took great care of me, she made sure I was okay and told me to stay in the bathroom as long as I needed to. Before I left she gave me a cup of water and baking soda to settle my stomach because I couldn’t stop throwing up, it worked wonders I was able to make it home in Birmingham Alabama. I just wanted to take the time and recognize Ms. Shannon for her great customer service and care for people. She deserves a raise...! Keep her around she’ll bring a lot of business!

text: I absolutely love the women that run this! First off it is such an adorable resturant, very clean and the food is amazing! But what stands out even more is the service! I have food allergies and it can be frustrating to go to a smaller resturant vs. A chain that has clearly listed allergens. I was nervous to order something and not sure if it would make me sick. She overheard me telling my husband I wasn't going to order because I didn't trust if I could have it or not. She was so kind and understanding. She went through the menu assure me of what I could have and making special substitutions. The result was one of the best salads I've ever had! We will definitely be back!

text: This has been my go to for gas every since the doors opened. All staff members behind the register and otherwise have always been the most accommodating and respectful. That seems to be changing. There are still one or two remaining that are pleasant to do business with. However there are also some there now who do not appreciate their jobs or us the customer.Recently when I bought gas I had to get change back. The cashier did not count the change to me she had it to me in a clump and I didn’t see one of the bills so I asked her if it was in there and very disgusted Lee she said yes it’s there and she rolled her eyes and turned around and walked away. That is not good customer service. She never thanked me for coming in when I went in to pay Nor at any time did she even produce a smile. Arrogant and condescending. I asked her name – she said J. I have always given this station five stars if I have to keep dealing with her I will move my business and tell others in the area how bad the cashiers have gotten recently.

name: Travis Engram
text:
Update: regional manager personally called me and validated my concerns. Says a fix is coming, admitted to network issues and apologized for staff and network issues. Taking a wait and see approach. And adding back some stars.

About one out of every three times I come in to use my MapcoExpress discount the gas pump times out, causing me to change pumps and lose my reward discount. Tonight I stood there for over 10 minutes waiting, which is what the screen said to do. I pressed the call attendant button many, many times, to no avail. I finally went inside, and there was no one in there. Looked around and finally was given the international sign for wait a minute from one of the three employees in the back. I waited and was again told it wasn't their fault and there is nothing they can do, which I already knew. You have a telecom issue and never fix it. I don't care if it is a corporate office issue, it affects me, my time, my mood, and my price of gas. I drive by 15 stations to come to your station and yet it's not your problem. I'm aware it is my problem, businesses with customer focused attitudes make my problem their problem. Maybe you could start there...

name: Christy Hales
text: The food here was amazing and the staff was very friendly and even gave us some fresh orange juice to sample.  The wait for our to-go order was on the long side and the prices were higher than most places nearby (about $8 for a sandwich), but the quality of the food was outstanding and it was well worth the wait and the price.  All of the produce is clearly very fresh and the portions were generous.  The sandwiches come with amazing seasoned chips (or crackers?  I'm not sure what they are other than delicious) and salsa as well as a few pieces of fresh fruit.  I can't wait for my next opportunity to go back.

name: Quinn Calvert
text:
A small place with a quaint sort of homely feel. I got the Sicily sandwich, and it was phenomenal - exactly the sort of Italian flavors I was looking for on a hot summer day. The sides are fairly limited, but the chips and salsa aren't bad. Couldn't help but feel the salsa was lacking something: a zest, tang, spice, idk. It just seemed a bit too bland.

But that's really the only demerit. Overall a great mix of value, flavor, and portion size.

text: I visit Huntsville often for leisure and dental meetings and happen to come across this cafe, I absolutely admire this cafe....The waitress was exceptionally sweet and the food was divine. This is a cafe that I'd highly recommend for breakfast or brunch..

name: Stephanie Pierce
text: I went to Sady's Bistro today, 4/18/15, with my mom and the experience wasn't great. I believe it opens at 8 and we got there around 8:45. When we walked in there was one lady ahead of us and she was told by the workers in the back that the server had not arrived yet. We had been waiting a few minutes when finally the server showed up. My mom ordered spinach and egg crepes and I ordered what I thought was a quesadilla with basil goat cheese. We sat down and my mom's crepes came out fairly quickly and I continued to wait. After maybe 10 minutes the server came back and said that they were out of basil goat cheese so I switched fr another and waited. While I was still waiting a couple that had ordered after us both got their meals and mine had yet to come. Finally after maybe 25 minutes mine finally arrived. it was 2 tiny toasted tortillas a few slices of tomato and a little cup of goat cheese and 2 pieces of bacon. When we asked why it had taken so long she basically just blamed the workers in the back and gave a rushed sorry as she walked away. I just found the whole experience very off-putting and do not think I will be returning.

name: Duncan Mills
text:
Honestly it just all around sucked.

The line/checkout was confusing, I did not know where to pay or wait for my food. My sub wasn’t made right in front of me like literally every other sub sandwich place. They got it served through the window then I got asked “what you want?” And they peel open your sandwich to add ingredients.

The food, albeit edible for a hungry shift worker, was pretty sad. All I wanted was a normal BLT sub sandwich with mayo, and some chips. Instead, I got served this weird but sad triple-decker pressed Texas toast BLT. I didn’t mind the non traditional approach, but the execution was bad. The Texas toast was smashed so thin I had this dense layer of mayonaise soaked bread to peel off my teeth. The bacon was cooked well but the lack of lettuce, tomato, and a normal sub bun kinda ruined it.

At least it was cheap, around $7.50, so at least it wasn’t an expensive mistake.

name: Jessica Heyer
text:
BEWARE!!  CARD SKIMMER ON CREDIT CARD MACHINE AT THE REGISTER INSIDE THE STORE.
When I used my debit card at this store on July 17, 2018, I was required to enter my pin # two times- once at the beginning of the transaction and again at the end of the transaction. I Asked the cashier why I was required to enter my pin twice and she quickly looked away nervously and didn't respond. I then turned the machine and looked closely at the side where cards are swiped. The machine appeared to have an overlay that had been mounted to the credit card machine. When I looked up, the cashier looked away quickly and would not make eye contact.

The following day, July 18, I began to see fraudulent charges posting to my bank account. I reported the charges to regions and was told by the bank manager that it appeared that someone had cloned my debit card. Regions is opening an investigation into the fraud.

TO THE OWNER OF THIS STORE-
YOUR EMPLOYEE (white female with brown hair, approx late 30s to 40s) that was working the register on July 17, 2018 around 1pm is a thief!!
If she stole from me, she'll steal from you and the rest of your customers!!

resp.text:
Thank you Erin for your review.  I am looking into this situation and please know that I take this issue  very serious.  I would love to speak to you to acquire more details . Country Convenience has never had this happen before.
Thank You   Patti Middleton  251-964-5674  or 251-747-7581

text: Now I remember why I do not buy cigarettes from Mapco. The price is always wrong ex. The sign said $4.49 but the price is $4.96 and it said buy 2 save $0.50 but that is not true either. What else are they cheating us on?

text: Broken seal, this speaks for itself.

text: Mapco is a great place to come & get gas, get food w/ Mapco rewards u can't go wrong!!

name: Andy King
text: Hounded for money 4 times in 10 minutes. Saw them scare a young woman.

name: Dee Bail
text: Clean store, nice facility.

name: gerald Howard
text: The cashiers at this Mapco were the rudest and most unprofessional I have ever seen! Every single time I visit! Especially, the tall lady. She acts as if you're borrowing gas and not paying for it. Mapco Publix and Chick-fil-A are known for their courteous employees, but this location is tearing your name down!

resp.text: We apologize for the experience you described and we can assure you that behavior goes against our culture standards. We have alerted the District Manager over that location to take swift action.

name: Charity Shackelford
text: I would like to take this time to share a wonderful experience at this location. I purchased product at this particular location tonight. After my purchase I got in my car and was pulling out of the lot when a wonderful man by the name of Aaron came running to my car with my phone I had left on the counter. Thank you so very much for having such an honest and caring person on your team. Aaron you have no idea how much that meant. You saved so many photos/video's, all memories that I could never get back if it hadn't been for you. THANK YOU!

resp.text: Thank you for leaving such a nice review. We are glad that you loved our services, our dedicated staff will be pleased to learn of your high praise.

name: Mikie Morris (Mikie)
text: It was a few yrs ago that I had visited this establishment and being that Im from Colorado I was happy to find a fuel station in the area that sold diesel fuel. The cashier that night was more than helpful in answering a couple of questions for me. So I can't say anything bad about this place it was definitely a brighter note in my horrendous trip to the Huntsville area.

resp.text: Mikie, We are happy to hear you had a positive experience at MAPCO! We value your input and encourage you to let us know more details about your experience with us.

name: Debra Tarbox
text: Never have problems except when I come when it's busy. The staff are polite and that's even after dealing with disagreeable people. No matter where you go there are idiot drivers and people who think everyone owes them. Bless the staff who endure this corner of this side of town.

resp.text: Debra, Thank you again and it really helps to have customers like you sharing feedback regarding our performance.

name: Tiffany Wallace
text: The door was wide open when I went inside the store last night to buy drinks. I sat at the register for about 5 minutes with no one at the desk or even in the store. The lady behind me went out to the patio to find a cashier, and one came back in only to tell us they were closed. It was close to 4 AM, yet they say they're open for 24 hours.... Needless to say, I left the drinks I was planning to buy at the register and walked out. I'm not happy with their service at all.

resp.text:
Tiffany, We apologize for the experience you described and we can assure you that we have alerted the team of operations over that location to take swift action and resolve this matter.
Please allow us to earn back your trust.

name: Reese B
text: Don’t go here if you expect to do a quick stop. They usually have about 10 employees mingling around with one person takin cash. God bless you if they start chatting with the cashier because that’s going to tack on another 10 minutes to your trip

name: Jessie Basinger
text: Door was not set on automatic it was opened up 2". When we watched a local cop open the door by hand and go into the bathroom we followed. They told us...paying customers in uniform also (emergency road service crew) that only cops are allowed in right now... I suggest EVERYONE GO ACROSS THE STREET TO SUNOCO!! Very nice staff and actually open 24 hrs.

name: Daniel Yearta
text: I try to make sure I spend the least amount of my time & money here, as possible. It's one of those places that just want to appear to be clean on the outside but on the inside it's kinda disgusting. Workers attitudes toward customers are based on the color of your skin, normally only one cashier during busiest times of day, bathrooms are always atrocious and/or missing toilet paper/hand towels/soap, and most food is over or under cooked, if it's not already pre packaged and over priced. I only stop here if it's all that's open, if it's actually open, and in case of extreme emergencies. I avoid it like the plague! Enter at your own risk.

name: Victor Brant
text: 6:35am on 5/22/19 - Come in - Jessica says "HI". Get my coffee and start to head up to register. Again the store manager(tall black man) is behind the register. Jessica is at a register that has about 10+ customers in line. He calls for the next person in line. This goes on for a couple of minutes. I am next inline to be called "next", he looks up and see's who I am and he walks off!! With more than 10+ customers still in line to be helped! The customer in front of me finishes and Jessica greats me with a smile. "Good morning, did you see that", I asked Jessica. "Yes I did", she replied. This is the 3rd time this employee has provided very poor customer service, almost to the point that I am taking offence to it. I am thinking that Mapco is not going to do anything about it since nothing has happened.  It is a real shame that 1 employee can ruin your whole day and make your stores attitude not very pleasant to visit or deal with. I hope that you will take ahold of this comment and actually do something about it.

resp.text:
Victor, We apologize for the experience you described and we can assure you that behavior goes against our culture standards. We have alerted the District Manager over that location to take swift action and resolve this issue.
Please allow us to earn back your trust.

name: kitt Tidwell
text: Was about to make a $30 dollar purchase but was trying to find saltine crackers. My black boyfriend who was carrying the charcoal we were going to buy got approached by the cashier even though she had 5 people still in her line. She told him we were taking too long and needed to hurry up pay and leave. He went to the line after I gave up on my crackers and I went ahead to the side and asked her what the issue was. She just glared at me and wouldn't answer. I requested her the number of the manager, she gave me a fake number I found out later, and then told me I needed to leave or she would call the cops. My boyfriend and I deal with people against interracial couples all the time but this was absolutely disgusting to be treated this badly.

resp.text: Kit, We apologize for the experience you described and we can assure you that behavior goes against our culture standards. We have alerted the District Manager over that location to take swift action and resolve this problem.

name: Amanda Lynn
text: I'm not sure why everyone is giving such poor reviews. My husband and I happened to love this store. The staff and COFFEE are amazing. I'm horrible with names but the lady with red hair is a delight. There is long lines and most of the time there is no creamer in the machine and the coffee bar is dosgusting. But if people would clean up after themselves and do a little self help at the coffee bar, it would go a long ways ! You see the ladies checking all the customers out. We don't go anywhere else for gas or cigarettes.

resp.text: Amanda, Thank you so much for your review!

text: This store rarly ever has coffee  made at 1:30 a.m. I generallt gwve ro go to another store revery day for my coffee

resp.text:
David,  We have alerted the upper management  over that location so that they may resolve this issue.
Please allow us to earn back your trust.

text: The coffee is #1 and the selection is GREAT! They're always busy and lines can get long but they make it up by the quickness and efficientcy of the employees, 2 - 3 minute wait tops!

resp.text: J, Thank you so much for your review!

resp.text: Leah, We do apologize for the experience you have described. We can assure you we have notified the  team of operations regarding this situation to ensure this matter will be resolved.

name: Michael Odom
text: 99% of the time the parking lot is full of people loitering and panhandling. The restrooms are always a mess, full of flies, and understocked. There ALWAYS a line at the register, either because they're slow or too busy chatting with their friends.

resp.text: Michael, We apologize for the experience you have described. We do hope that you continue to be our guest at MAPCO and allow us to make your next visit a better experience.

name: J Goodwin
text: Went in to get coffee, a bite, & smokes but instead of getting served was told they was closed & wouldn't be open for another 30 mins when the sign on the door states plainly that they was open, some guy that doesn't even work there is the one whom relayed the message while the employee at the counter didn't even check up, I asked why the sign says 24 hours & his reply is that I could get gas at the pump with a card, there's a lot of gas stations that you can get gas at the pump after hours & they don't have a sign that says they're open for 24 hours cause that wouldn't be the truth, so why are y'all any different? I went to a different Mapco, they was open, & it wasn't 30 mins later. Your online hours also state that y'all are open 24 hrs, so I wasted gas, my time, & was lied to! If you look up Chevron that isn't 24hrs but can still get gas 24hrs hours with a card at the pump their store hours are correct, y'all should change your sign at the door & online to the correct service you provide.

resp.text: We apologize for the experience you described. We can assure you that behavior goes against our culture standards. We have alerted the Operational Leader over that location to take swift action.

name: Jeremy West
text: Consistent Mapco

resp.text: Thanks for placing your trust in us and your willingness to share. We always appreciate hearing back from our guest.

name: Terry Walker
text: I've just returned from this store. The syrup was out on the Coke fountain dispenser so I was only getting the carbonated water. A young man, his first day, understood the problem and relayed the message to another worker. I understand busy days, busy times, so I pulled out a chair and waiting. If ANYONE had acknowledged me at all - "sorry, ma'am, we haven't forgotten you" - but the other two employees wouldn't make eye contact with me at all. I'd be sitting there still waiting if they would've just acknowledged me. I hope a manager will review with them some proper customer service techniques. T

text: The worst gas station in the history of gas stations! Most pumps are out of order, card readers don't work, and employees are garbage.

resp.text: Taylor, We apologize for the experience you described and we can assure you this information will be passed on to  operations  over that location to take swift action and resolve this matter.

name: draydre mccoy
text: My experience on 10/23/18... I went into the store tonight I only had change and a few dollars to get me some gas the cashier had a line of 7 people and was in the midst of having a conversation instead of waiting on customer when I finally got to the register I stepped beside the customer in front of me and began to count out my change the cashier in the store young black male with dreadlocks working the register seem to have a issue with me counting out my change because he had a lot of change in his drawer. I'm sorry sir but it's your job to count change. you're the one who chose the job of being a cashier in a gas station so you need to learn to deal with change. It's your job..

text: Absolutely horrible place. Staff is completely rude and very SLOW. Homeless people and bummes everywhere.

text: I live within walking distance and have tried this location a few times out of convenience. Each time, the check out wait time is absolutely obsurd (about 8-12 min waits), slow-paced/undertrained staff struggle to keep lines down, and homeless people frequently panhandle INSIDE the store as well as outside.

name: Patrick Grijalva
text: I recently quit smoking so I'm thankful I won't be returning to this store, and I will make sure to get gas elsewhere as well.  The longest, most frustrating lines in town and other than a couple standouts,  the most annoyingly inept staff of all the Mapcos.  It seems to stem from poor management.

name: Kayla S
text: Easily the worst Mapco in Huntsville. Consistently understaffed with employees that have little to no understanding of customer service or money handling. This store is a black mark on Marco's brand. Its so bad even our law enforcement have stopped making this a rest stop. You will be here for 20 minutes if you need ANYTHING from a cashier. And if they run out of any change at all before you check out, they will take 10 minutes to restock their drawer instead of continuing to take customers and getting change as needed. Most employees will not ID for cigarettes until a manager is present. I don't think any of them have completed high school. All of them are rude as hell too. This is the 4th day in a row I have stopped at this gas station due to work, and all 4 times it has cost me a lot of time. Go to any other Mapco but avoid this one at all costs.

name: Terry Dixon
text: Daily we go there after the bars close and there always asut down. How does a 24 hr store shut down.

name: Carla Lester
text:
I have contacted the manager to tell her the problems with this store and they said give me a chance to fix the problems..... Well here i sit at 4:50 am again waiting to get in the store. Website says "Open 24 hours, and they tell me that they closed between 4 and 4:20... Hummm Now why did i rush to get here before 4?
Now usually i leave and go to the Mapco on 72 which may I add that store is awsome. People is nice, store clean, coffee made and they update around 1 in the morning.
I sit here watching customer after customer pull up and pull away mad. 😠..... Even our officers that protect this store and is called out over and over to this store...
I totally get they gave to upload there system but they should All do it at the same time every day. And change there website.
May I add that this morning i helped this little lady that needed gas to get to the hospital because her husband was being transported by ambulance all she had was cash she was in 😢 tears.. I used my mapco card with my pay pal and got her gas...
Come inn set a certain time around 2 in the morning when you are less busy.... I would think that 4 to 7 in the morning would be a busy part of your day.....

name: Marissa Wiles
text: Very disappointed in this store. Went in with my husband today to look around. Was trying to just find some cute jewelry. Unfortunately, we were subjected to a soap opera from the "manager" behind the counter and her friend in the store. We got to hear all about how the gentleman in her life was still talking to his ex and she would beat his a**. This is not professional for a work environment. The conversation was loud enough to be heard across the entire store. We left without purchasing anything due to the atmosphere there. I'll be highly surprised if I visit again.

resp.text:
Hi Marissa,

My name is Connie - I am the owner and manager of Fanci Free. Thank you for taking time to leave a review and bringing this incident to my attention.  I was not in the store on the day of your visit, but as soon as I heard what happened I made several unsuccessful attempts to contact you. I discovered this written review about your experience only last week.

I wish to extend my sincere apologies to you and your husband. I want you to know I have personally addressed the situation.

At Fanci Free, we value each and every one of our customers. We have a long-standing reputation of making our boutique and café a place where everyone feels happy and leaves happy. I am so glad that you enjoyed the quality and appeal of Fanci Free (as reflected in your ratings) - but on the day of your visit, we fell short of our overall mission.

As a token of our appreciation for your patronage, and to make amends, I invite you to return and enjoy a free meal with us. Then I will be happy to help you find that cute jewelry you were looking for - we have plenty to choose from!

Please call and ask for me (Connie Dismukes).

I look forward to meeting you and your husband. Thank you again for your comments and helping us to continue providing the best service and customer experience in the downtown Prattville area.

Connie Dismukes, Owner & Manager - Fanci Free Café & Boutique

text:
FANTASTIC food! It's an unexpected pleasure to be found in downtown. There's more seating outside than in, so plan accordingly. The volume of orders I saw were carry-out.

Order was served quickly and correctly. Great place.

text: Stopped by on our vacation. It's not too far from the interstate. It's a small place, but their food was amazing. I got the best Philly cheese steak I've ever had there. I highly recommend it. Nice and friendly staff as well. Will be stopping by again.

text: I got the BLT with pimento cheese, mom got the chicken salad sandwich, and we split broccoli salad and strawberry pretzel salad. Everything was delicious, the place is clean, the people are nice and service was fast! All around wonderful :)

name: April Davis
text: The service and food are Wonderful! I love the Philly and homemade strawberry pretzel salad. :) I recommend Wildwood to everyone.

name: Levi Westbrook
text:
Modern and young with the flavor of that old Southern tradition serving as a backdrop.

Beautiful original brick exposed on the eastern wall.

This is a family business with a unique menu, featuring original creations by the owner & friends. I was pleasantly surprised to walk in and find banana puddin' with meringue topping just like my grandma makes sitting on a hutch behind the register.

Chicken salad sandwich rocked me to the core. A number of original Reubens with mouthwatering descriptions I'm kicking myself for not trying line the menu. Philly cheese steak seems to be their best seller.

The small kitchen staff will (and did) bust their butts to make sure everyone is happy (we visited during a crowded convention day). I wish I worked at a business in Athens Square, I'd be a regular at this quaint little eatery.

Highly recommend if you're coming through. Something for everyone. Thanks to the owners & staff for a great experience.

text: This is my favorite place to grab a bite to eat in town. Small place with not a lot of space but awesome food and worth the wait!

name: Bill Rice
text: They took advantage of my teenage son.  The pump handle stuck and wouldn't stop after the tank filled.  He ran to get them to shut off the pump after getting gas all over his clothes.  This was clearly a problem with the pump as they constantly are having problems at this location.  Then they blamed him and charged him nearly $40 for all the gas that was pumped.  When I returned an hour later to ask for a refund, all of the pumps were shut off, as shown in the pictures, because they had another problem.  They refused a refund, refused to look at video to show that my car savvy son did nothing that could cause this problem, and forwarded my info to another manager.  Bottom line:  the gas price may be cheap but they are crooked, disrespectful, and refuse to admit the pumps are broken.  I'm looking forward to the opening of a Kroger gas station just down 72.

If I go even in the same day 2 times my will get charged 42 dollars once and then my I can goes few hours later and then I get charged almost 50 dollars. I was told that it was because the product was not being put in right in the register by 2 different managers. Just letting you know that you should make sure your being charged right because the employee working will not care they always have some excuse like oh they went up but if you go the next day wow price is back lower again.I have made complaint but nobody seems to care and have made complaint online with no response so I guess I will have to go somewhere else and my wifesince they have charged me over by hundreds of dollars this year. You won't get my and my wife's money anymore which is usually together 600 a month worth of business counting gas and such.. this by the way is the mapco that is the newer one county line and 72 in Madison AL. I was suppose to have the next day off because I've worked 13 days straight at the other store, the manager gave the other employee my two days off. Even though she knew that my schedule follows from the other store to here. She completely ignore me and had my scheduled for almost 100 hours for the week... And another thing too, WHY WOULD YOU HAVE 4 PEOPLE OPEN AND ONLY HAVE ME CLOSING!?!? Second day on the job, all of a sudden I've gotten very sick from something in the store. By the way, NONE OF THE FOUNTAIN DRINKS WORK! And If you smell something funky in the store, it's sewage backup. And I would definitely not eat at this store either. And then the third day comes, I was fired instantly....

Yea it's more expensive but atleast nothing is wrong when I'm there.

name: Donna Couch
text:
Sat, Mar 12, Madison, AL corner of County Line and Hwy 72, store 8897
Did enjoy this Mapco since its opening due to convenience. However, today multiple pumps weren't operational, and three different keypads weren't functioning forcing us to move around an already busy station.  We settled on one that flowed very slow.  A young lady beside us was charged before $.01 before the pump shut down.  We walked in to let the attendant behind the counter know, and he said nothing while shrugging his shoulders, twice, and proceeded to ignore us.  Mapco should be ashamed of not only allowing a relatively still new station, in a busy spot, to be so inadequate, but also for hiring such a poor excuse for customer service.  We'll be finding another station, which is also disappointing because this one was convenient.  Boo!!!

text: The Italian sandwich is so good ( I heat it up)   big enough for two meals.   I love the crown filets...they cook up nicely and melt in your mouth.  Service with a smile.

name: Danny Neaves
text: Okay, I've heard a little bit about this place from word of mouth. Didn't realize they prepared food for you to eat on site. I thought they were only a butcher shop type of grocery store. They are a restaurant, and that is why I came by to try them out. I had a burger, and wow it was really good. It is a big burger, fresh, thick, and juicy. There are other sandwich style meals they offer with a variety of different meats and veggies. I will be back to get some cuts of meat to try out and to try some of the other sandwiches too. I have only had it the one time, but I would recommend it based on what I have had so far. Looking forward to trying some other stuff too!!

resp.text: Thanks for stopping in to check us out! We’re so glad you enjoyed your burger and hope you’ll stop back in again soon!

text: I drove through today to get lunch.  This cheeseburger is solid.  The people here are so nice, too.  I'm gonna make it a point to drive through here more often.

text: We just had the Italian hoagies ( with their fresh made bread ) and heated up. It was the best sandwich I’ve ever had. Way more quality Meat and flavors than subway , I’ll get the hamburger next time. It’s unlike any other around

text: The price for two usda prime filets was very high, considering I was unable to taste a difference from that of a grocery store chain usda prime steak. I overpaid expecting a better steak and was let down. Cant say I would make the trip to smiley brothers again. Staff was friendly but for $60 a lb I’ll try somewhere else next time.

name: Cre Hill
text: Best Burger I’ve had in a long time!! Fresh, seasoned and of great quality!

name: Julian king
text: Food is amazing. Service is impeccable. Not many places you go to that the owner is working the drive thru and greeting everyone. Highly recommend.

resp.text: Thank you so much for your kind words Julian! We hope to see you again soon!

name: Cindy McRee
text: What a unique find! Dryed, aged beef! Unique cheeses you cannot hardly get anywhere else. Too many unique homemade items to mention such as pickles, sauerkraut, breads, etc. As must for an early evening of a glass of wine, a few cheeses, sliced meats and quality conversation with a friend or significant other.

resp.text: Thanks so much Cindy! We hope you’ll visit again soon :)

name: Life Is Brewtiful
text: I absolutely loved this place! The owner and sous chef we're incredibly helpful, attentive, and polite. They were very knowledgeable of their products, provided samples of anything requested and seemed to have a genuine passion for their profession. I loved being able to see the high end and made in house products be made either through the window into the kitchen or in their air drying system for their meats. The sandwiches we're absolutely delicious and made with an obviously higher caliber of product quality than you will find anywhere else in the area. And for the (on average) $10 you get chips and a drink as well. You can even call in and pick up your order at a later time! Now some people will say that the prices are too high, and to a point I agree. However, I also appreciate that this is a premium product with supurb quality which demands and justifes a higher price. Seems fair to me. In my opinion this place is too good for Pelham.

resp.text: Thank you so much for your kind words. We're glad you decided to stop in and we hope you've enjoyed everything!

name: Robyn Arrieche
text: Let’s face it, they know what they are doing here. I had the Wagyu Pastrami sandwich toasted that was VERY good. However, my only critique was that there was an overpowering taste of saltiness coming from the mustard or the sauerkraut which was disappointing because the meat was soooo good.

name: Rick McCoy
text: Best in town. Bar none.

name: Doug Cole
text:
Went for the first time last night and wasn't disappointed.  Criss was extremely knowledgeable about the various cuts of meat and the dry aging process.  I felt like I was attending a culinary class.  The meal was excellent!
I'll definitely be back for seconds!

name: Taylor Hart
text: It was SO good. That Jon Green guy is a dream.  That meatloaf sandwich though.... it's a winner.

name: Danita Ryan
text: I stopped in from work at about 4:00 p.m. to grab a chicken salad sandwich. I rate it a 10, it was delicious and fresh. Smiley Brothers is a different place but when you walk in the door you know that you are about to receive great service and wonderful food. I recommend it to everyone. I love their customer service because if you don't know they have time to talk you through it and you can have it your way.

resp.text: Thank you for such a kind review! We’re so glad you enjoyed everything and hope you’ll stop by and see us again soon!

name: Dennis Tymkiw
text: Prime grade dry-aged steaks cut to order. Loaded baked potatoes ready to warm up and devour. They pickle their corned beef and make their own pastrami. Select cheese and wine. A jewel of a store with a knowledgeable staff. Foodies-don't miss this place.

resp.text: Thanks for the kind words Dennis!

name: Dennis Tymkiw
text: Prime grade dry-aged steaks cut to order. Loaded baked potatoes ready to warm up and devour. They pickle their corned beef and make their own pastrami. Select cheese and wine. A jewel of a store with a knowledgeable staff. Foodies-don't miss this place.

resp.text: Thanks for the kind words Dennis!

text: Outstanding Italian beef sandwich today. Highly recommend

name: Christina Klockow Runnels
text: We have eaten there a few times and everything we have gotten has been delicious! Everything is fresh and seasoned perfectly and their cookies are out of this world! My favorite is the pimento cheese and my husband always gets the club sandwich. Looking forward to trying the chicken salad next! We are so lucky to have this gem in our town!

resp.text: Thank you so much for the kind review! We’re so glad you liked what you tried and can’t wait to hear what you think of our house made chicken salad!

name: rene generoso
text: Great meat great cheese and great high prices haha

name: Marnie Reineke
text: Highly recommend if you are in the Birmingham area!  They prepared an amazing meal to go for our daughter’s soccer team and everyone enjoyed it. Terrific selection of delicious meats, cheeses  and other specialty foods  that works for one or a large group. Can’t say enough good things about both  the shop and the people who work there.

resp.text: Marnie, you're too kind! Thank you for such a thoughtful review, we're so glad you enjoyed your Smiley Brothers experience!

name: Darlene Talton
text:
Smiley Brothers has great deli sandwiches. They make most all of their ingredients on site. Everything is fresh made. They put plenty on your sandwich. They have a large selection of cheeses.
They do catering and cooler packages. Friendly and helpful employees.

resp.text: Thank you Darlene for your kind words!

name: Vintowsi Farms
text:
Traveling from Sacramento, California to Florida in an RV and stopped for a sandwich. Little did we know this would be the best sandwich of our trip!    So delish!
Criss knows quality, and he delivers that.
Wow, soooooo good and fresh!
Will stop again on our way back to Sacramento.

resp.text: We’re so glad you stopped by and that you loved your sandwich! THANK YOU!

name: QuantumPolagnus
text: My wife and I came here with no idea what they even sold.  We found out they sell lunch, so my wife got their Special Burger and I got a bowl of their Tomato Soup.  They showed us around and told us more about what they do as the food was being prepared.  Apparently the burger was a house recipe combination of different steaks ground together with butter, parsley, etc.  Suffice it to say that the burger was one of the best we have ever had.  The soup was also really good and creamy with shredded gouda and croutons on it.

resp.text: Thank you so much for the kind review and for stopping by to give us a try! We so glad you enjoyed what you tried and hope you’ll come back and see us again soon!

name: Scott Lamoreaux
text: We have had almost every sandwich on the menu and each one has top quality Meats, cheese and bread. All of the take-home meats and items are as good as you will find in this area. Of course it's not cheap because it's the best. Also the only place I know of locally that has true dry aged beef.

resp.text: Hi Scott, thanks for the kind words! We're glad you've enjoyed the sandwiches and hope you'll come back and see us again soon!

name: Candace Herron
text: Great roast beef sandwich!  Also picked up some house made sausages and cheese.  I plan to come back for some dry aged steaks soon.

resp.text: Thanks for the kind review Candace!

name: Garrett Bowling
text: I finally branched out and tried something other than the beloved Meatloaf Sandwich....OMG am I glad I did because the Wagyu pastrami sandwich was AMAZING! The tangy house made pickles, cut through the rich fatty goodness of the Wagyu. The whole grain mustard and swiss cheese round out the flavors and it is served on wonderfully toasted Rye. Now the only problem I have is what to try next!

name: Chris Ashley
text: Bland sandwiches. Roast beef especially bad possibly expired or old.  Had club, roast beef, and chik salad.

name: Em
text: Wonderful place with friendly staff!

resp.text: Thanks Emily!

name: David Price
text: The staff was super friendly and helpful.  I had their cheese burger with a lettuce wrap instead of bun.  In my opinion, it is the best cheese burger in Shelby County.

resp.text: Thank you David for such a nice review! We’re so glad you enjoyed your burger!

name: Jonathan Eidson
text: The meat here is a premium product, so expect to pay a premium price. You’ll end up with a better steak from your own grill than you’d get at any place outside of a $100+ per plate fine dining restaurant for much less. The staff is friendly and willing to spend time discussing their products with you. Definitely will go to again for a fine steak dinner at home with the wife or other special meals.

resp.text: Thank you for your kind review! Please come back and see us soon!

name: Tommy Barberini
text: Had an amazing sandwich but you better bring your appetite! Dry/wet aged meat available as well. Will definitely be back.

resp.text: Thanks Tommy! Hope you and your appetite are able to stop by again soon :)

name: Bill Burn
text: Had the Smiley Burger over the weekend and this is absolutely the best burger in bham! This thing is stacked tall and they apparently have butter in their beef mix! The cheddar is melted over the meat dripping down the toppings. They have lots of great sandwiches, but this is my new favorite! I would pit it against any burger in bham!! If you haven’t been in here yet, check it out. Great wine, cheese, and sandwiches. Chef Josh and the guys are always polite and helpful!

resp.text: Thank you Bill for such a kind review! We’re so glad you enjoyed your Smiley Brothers Burger!

name: garrett bowling
text: Never been here before today but I had the Meatloaf sandwich and it was INCREDIBLE! Will definitely be ordering it again!

resp.text: Thanks for stopping in and giving us a try! We’re so glad you loved your sandwich and look forward to seeing you again!

name: Lorraine Reeves
text:
From the moment you walk in, you are greeted by a friendly and helpful staff.  Fresh vegetables and any type of infused olive oils you can imagine.  The cheese display is incredible, and the staff is more than happy to give you a sample of any you would like to try.  Let's not forget the meat!  You can see the dry aging of beef in process.  It takes about thirty days to age the beef.  I bought a ready to cook meal that includes chunks of prime beef, carrots, onions, celery, potatoes, a half bulb of garlic, tomato paste and a red wine jus.  Cooked it in my dutch oven, and it was perfect.  I didn't have to cut up the vegetables or meat, so it was a great time-saver.  Did I mention the filets?  Bought two dry-aged and they grill to fork tender.  The flavor is certainly better than regular filets from the grocery store.  All meat is butchered in-house, by well-trained chefs and the house-made sausage is unique, yes classic.  I also bought pork chops that must have been over an inch thick.
I highly recommend you buy from this specialty food store!

resp.text: Lorraine, thank you SO MUCH for your incredibly kind words. We strive everyday to make sure each guest loves their Smiley Brother experience both in shop and once they take their purchases home. We hope you come back to see us soon!

name: SometimeAfterTwoAM
text: It's about time Birmingham got an authentic italian deli.  I can honestly say I have experienced the real thing in NYC, Long Beach, and LA and this is comparable to all 3 of those.  I had the 6" Avondale and it was more than I could eat.  I don't see how anyone could eat a 12" alone.  I didn't weigh the meat but I'd guess this was 2X the amount of meat & cheese as you'd get on a 12" from Subway or Firehouse Subs and that's on a 6" sandwich.  Bread was gourmet and excellent.  Probably the largest selection of unique sodas and bottled beverages I've ever seen at a restaurant.  I'd estimate there are more than 50 different drinks NOT including traditional Coke and Pepsi products.  Friendly staff made me want to return ASAP.  You cannot go wrong with this true authentic italian deli.

text: I hate to say this because I believe in having a light hearted atmosphere in your work environment but they do it a little too much where they screw up orders. The first time I was there I had order for take out and they were busy and 5 people before me ended up getting the order wrong they even got one table's order wrong twice. Then I get my order and I checked it just to make sure and sure enough they had gotten my order wrong and it's because the whole time the workers are constantly joking around with each other that they aren't paying attention to what they are doing. Then the second time I order a sandwhich and salad and I was an idiot not to check my bag because they didn't even put it in the bag and it was the main thing I wanted out of the whole order because it was for my paralyzed grandfather who I take care of full time. I get him Lenny's as a treat and don't get much time to get away from the house for this and the manager really didn't act like it was a big deal. We pay good money for your sandwhiches I shouldn't have to waste gas to correct your screw ups just because you think it's better to not be focused on job. I will never return to them. I have even had other people tell me they stopped going to Lenny's because they always screw up their order because of the joking around. Get it together.

text:
Okay so this review is a bit unique, because over all it was an enjoyable experience. I came in with A LOT OF COINS, to cash in with the coin star machine. Mostly pennies, over 10,000 of them actually haha. And the employee (not specifying gender as I don't want to misuse pronouns on someone that I have no clue on their choice of gender or lack thereof) was so kind, patient and professional. Thank you!

Now the not so good, there was an employee that was working the closest register to the coinstar that the other employee refered me to go cash in my coinstar vouchers with, and the employee flatly, rudely, denied exchanging my vouchers, then making a face that one would only expect to see if the employee was changing a babies diaper for the first time and looked behind to the other employee at the second register stating "uuuughh I just don't wannnaaaa I don't liiiikeee ittttt" seriously? Alright, I'll go back to the nice one :) needless to say my vouchers were promptly cashed out and apologies were made, which was so nice, thank you employee at the customer service desk, you were awesome and made my experience Great. You need a raise and a promotion.

name: Mrs “Melana114” White
text:
On multiple occasions they have not had sale items in stock, even on the first day of a sale.

Made the 60 mile trip to purchase  the whole tenderloin for $7.99 lb. The senior lady who works in the meat department was sarcastic and rude, definitely not in the correct line of work. Said they only had the $16.99 lb tenderloin but the other would be in stock the following morning. Refused our request to allow a substitution at a discount.

So, we make a SECOND 60 mile trip only to be told by another gentleman "oh, we haven't been able to order any".  How it goes from coming in today to never even being ordered is beyond me, but somebody isn't telling the truth. Then the same senior lady remarks, oh yall are the ones from yesterday. No apology for the inconvenience, nothing.

Asked for a manager and explain how we've now made two 60 mile trips. He just shrugs it off saying the ads were made 2 weeks ago and they just weren't able to get it in stock. I asked if we could at least get a raincheck or the $16.99 at a discount. NOPE. "In these times " they just can't predict blah blah blah.  I pointed out that in these times, a simple update to apps and websites would remove misleading sales they know they can't fulfill.

At the same time I was speaking to the manager, my husband was speaking to the butcher about just getting one of the 16.99 lb tenderloins and he says, oh they're all gone, we used them as substitutes for customers yesterday. (WOW. Must have been friends or family because they sure wouldn't do it for us!)

Poorly managed. Poor customer service. No longer worth the trip.

text: Ordinarily, I would recommend this particular Winn Dixie, but today is not that day. Over the past few months, the amount of out of date product has been very prevalent. Three out of the five items I purchased were out of date (only realizing this after I had gotten home) and the worst one was out of date by six months. Please be mindful of what you're purchasing here. I really hope this doesn't continue to be a thing, because this store really is a good alternative to the other establishments within the area.

text:
The service has been much better than of late. The recent remodel was really nothing more than a few new display fixtures in the produce and bakery department and basically flipping the store around. It is much harder to locate products you bought on a regular basis. There is a certain individual that works in customer service that provides NO SERVICE. If asked about something she acts as if you are bothering her. Too many times I’ve had issues only to find out the manager on duty was not available. The fact that I enjoy interacting with the younger cashiers and the ones that stock and front the shelves is the only reason I continue to go back. Another large grocery store is only a few miles further and I’ve moved my larger purchases there and only buy small amount of food products to fill in if not available at the other store and I buy medication at Winn Dixie as the pharmacy staff is outstanding.

Two years ago I would give this store 5 stars but today it is hit or miss on quality service and leaning more towards miss most visits.

Another cashier cane over and asked what she was doing then she took my phone and tried again to find it. Either way it wasn't there and she looked at me like I was crazy instead of just simply going to the aisle to locate the price. She took the items of my bill and told  me I could talk to a manager. They don't have as much variety as Publix, which is another minute or two away, but they'll have pretty much anything a middle-class family will need. Good location as well, pretty much adjacent to a handful of residential communities, people will encounter it first before Publix or Walmart when heading towards downtown Anniston or Oxford.

name: Ramona Barber
text: I went to buy two drinks, a good living cola fizz and a naked green machine, the naked smoothie had a $1.99 under both flavors. At the register the new employee, Tammy, said the smoothie was $3.49 I told her it's priced here at $1.99. She went to the food deli and got this blonde who came with me so I could show her. She pointed to the drink on the other side of the shelf, so I asked then why is the $1.99 straight under the naked smoothies. She goes around to the back of the shelf when she comes out her exact words were "they are just misshelfed." I asked "since they are the price advertised that's what I'm getting it for right." She procced to tell me "no I'm not but we have cheaper drinks if you can't afford it." On top of all that she said it in front of four customers, which one female customer who was buying the same drink said I'll just go to pilot across street where they dont mistreat they're customers. So I bought the cola fizz and ask the cashier who told me her name was Tammy. Then I ask Tammy how to contact the manager she looked behind her at the blonde from the food area who shook her head no and Tammy said she couldn't give that information out so I ask what the blonde employees name was and she tried to say she didn't know it. After one or two other customers put their things down and left the store saying they wouldn't ever be back as will I unless the nameless blonde does not work there at all, for her very rude and unprofessional behavior. I would still like to talk to her manager because I've never been so humiliated in my life. Please fix this horrible employee with the attitude problem. False advertisements can be pretty harsh in the state of Alabama.

name: Tom S
text: They have a $50 pump limit. Only visit for fuel if you like to run your card for multiple transactions and keep an eye on your bank statement as the pos system here tends to double charge but Mapco blames everyone's bank instead of fixing the new pos system. Talking to management, staff, and customer service only confirms that its an IT problem but months later and still isn't fixed. If you are planning on spending < $50 at the pump then you should be fine

text: It's been over a year since I've been there but I figured I'd speak up. The food was good. Look, it's not the Carnegie Deli but for Birmingham, AL, it's brilliant. Best I remember it was a little pricey but nothing out of the ordinary. The service was friendly and fast. I would recommend it.

name: HJ Sullivan
text:
The food is okay, but it is heavily overpriced. The Russian Ruben I has was definitely not worth the $12.99 price-tag. The waitress brought out a pickles, celery, and carrot basket to our table. The pickles tasted horrible to me and it killed my expectation of a deli in this area. However, the waitress was pleasant and the atmosphere was nice.

Overall, I could not see myself returning when I can just go to Jimmy John's or a nearby grocery store for a mediocre sandwich.

name: David Wakefield
text: Best deli food in Birmingham and also some unique stuff like Corned Beef Hamburgers. One of my favorite places in Birmingham to eat. I've been over 50 times and only ever had one and experience and the owner was very quick to take care of it.

name: david oremland
text:
I like sandwiches, I like deli.  Max's is terrific in both regards.  Top notch food, large portions, fair prices.  I'm from the NY area, so you don't expect to find such good deli in Birmingham.  This place is excellent.

And by the way.  Kudo's to you Steve for expressing yourself.  Kudo's to supporters for standing up for Max's.  Its a sad day in the US when a small group of angry radicals want to threaten a business owner for expressing himself and using freedom of speech.

Keep up the good work!!!

name: Borden Burns
text: Restaurants this great are few and far between. I've never had a reuben sandwich this good anywhere. I'm also a big fan of their hot dogs and hamburgers. I would also recommend trying their latkes and knish. Fabulous food all around. I've never ever had a bad meal.

name: Andrew Mobley
text: Excellent food. I came in for lunch after reading the Huffington Post article. The food was fantastic, the owner was a delight to speak with, and the waitress refilled my drink several times before I was even finished with it. The lamb burger with feta cheese was perhaps the best burger i've ever had.

name: B.A. Callahan

Kids (and adults) love the free micro ice cream treat at the end. Keto friendly salads my favorite is the Turkey Cobb and Cuban sandwich on sourdough if going the combo route sub chips for veggies or sweet potato fries. Management was nice enough to credit is the price of the pizza.

text: I wish that I would have taken a picture of this pitiful looking salad that I ordered for $9.10. I ordered the grilled chicken salad.   It comes with lettuce, pickles, cucumbers, green olives, boiled egg, tomato, chicken and cheese plus dressing.  What I received was a big bowl of lettuce with 2 pickles,  2 cucumber slices, 5 olives some shredded cheese,  2 cherry tomatoes cut in half, a half a boiled egg cut into 2 and a small piece of chicken breast cut into 4 pieces.  I opted out of dressing but still. We asked for more toppings and what we got was exactly the same amount minus the chicken, didn't get any more meat. Overall the salad isn't worth $9.10. For the money we're not sure if we're ever going back.

I definitely recommend you to stop by.

name: pj P
text: We were traveling up I-65 and stayed overnight in Prattville AL. We looked on google for a local "breakfast" that wasn't a chain restaurant. CHAPPY'S came up. Unfortunately we got there AFTER they quit serving breakfast. Mike (owner/manager?), in consult with the kitchen staff, offered to fix us breakfast. The food was delicious, served promptly. The wait staff was very pleasant and helpful. Kourtney, our waitress, was SO very attentive! I'D DEFINITELY  GO  THERE AGAIN. The menu had a wide selection of choices!

name: UnbiasedReport
text: One of the things that I really admire about Chappy's Deli is their sandwiches. There is no competition for it. They have a wide assortment to choose from and they are always put together so nicely and neatly. My job typically gets deli sandwiches and chips from them often. That make good for a quick meal. I suggest getting the tuna fish sandwich and also the chicken salad sandwich is great too.

name: Christopher Martin
text: Love Chappy's! Great food, fair price, and wonderful staff! Parking in the back is better since there's an actual lot.

Prices are very reasonable & food was terrific. Omelet was fluffy & well-filled. Breakfast croissant was very tasty.  Will definitely visit again soon.

text: Great food @ service

name: Ashley Winters

We love our fav server Jessica she’s the best and remembers all our our favs we always ask for her when we can.

Gosh I was so excited to find a place with great customer service. My first trip here was awesome. But then when I brought my date over a second time, it looked like two of the employees touched each other behind the counter... Gross.

Anyway maybe it was just a one time thing... So I dropped my review 2 stars.

I saw someone who wasn't my waitress take our salads to 2 different tables then go past our table,I didn't see where she went for a minute or 2 and then she walks up to our table saying did you order a salad. My salad looked like some had been eaten off the top, I asked what are you doing and why did you take our salads to all those other tables?She just gave me a stupid look.I said what happened to the top of my salad, she spur around and said I'll bring you another one.she finally brought me another one in about 10 minutes. We will NEVER go back. Very rude people!

name: Marlon Bonner
text: home sweet home

name: Brian Kravitz
text:
Food’s decent. Not exactly what I would term a “Deli.”  More like a “Diner,” than a Deli. A deli will typically (not always, but usually) have a meat counter with assorted luncheon meats, salads, and fishes for sale. None here. They serve hot soups, hot/cold sandwiches, burgers, etc. typical diner food.

I wish the tri-county area actually had a Deli. I’d love a REAL barrel soaked kosher pickle.

name: E C
text: Breakfast was great. Had the veggie omelet & it was cooked perfectly. And the biscuit melted in my mouth. Hazel really took care of me. This Chappys is much better than the one on the east side of Montgomery. Will definitely be back!

name: Rachel Turner
text:
Good food, decent prices. HORRIBLE service. My family and I went during non-peak hours (late Saturday afternoon, maybe five tables were full) and had to wait to be seated for longer than necessary. I say this as several employees looked at us but didn't even say hi or that someone would be with us. Finally got seated. I then had to go find someone to take our order .... Again unnecessary as there were about 5 servers working a hand full of tables. Food was good and came in an ok amount of time. Ordered a milkshake to go for our kiddo....waited over 10 minutes. Finally had to go up to the counter where they were like "here!" And handed it to me as if I was an annoyance to them.

Wouldn't go back.

Order was placed/paid for from Springfield, IL to be delivered in your local area (Prattville, AL) to my Grandma. The transaction was flawless. She is 83 and had been left alone by her grown son, Elbert Jones, w barely any food. The driver Henry was wonderful. Did not get frustrated or visibly irritated I did not know exactly where she was, as I live in IL. He powered thru and found her home's actual name, Crestview Cottages. Grandma is 83 and would never be able to order food online. Chappy's Deli was wonderful, fast, and according to Gma, Fantastic!!
It was our first time and will definitely not be the last!!!

I was a big fan of this place when they were 24 hours. Now i prefer krogers. They open at 7 and close at ~8-10. Between the oblivious patrons blocking the path, the 'buy me' displays everywhere and the daytime stocking carts it's very frustrating just to move around in the store. There is no room. This isn't the employee's fault as employee's aren't displays or stocking carts. This is a managerial fault. Have daytime stocking or 'buy me' displays. Don't clutter the aisles with both. If I had to sum up my review it's just 'store very cluttered'.

I don't have the same frustrations moving around in other grocery stores. This is a walmart specific problem.

I was shopping last night and, out of the blue as is soooooo common with severe vertigo, I went into a panic attack and was almost in tears as I raced to the front of the store to check out and leave, and that sweet girl immediately noticed something was wrong.  I told her I was just trying to check out quickly because I was on the verge of a severe panic attack, and she raced around to me and put her arms around me and spoke the sweetest, kindest words, and I knew she was a gift straight from God!!  She checked me out and had me take a seat on the bench right up front and across from her checkout line, and just kept talking to me in between her other customers.  GIVE THAT GIRL A PROMOTION AND A RAISE!!

They were not attentive to me or any other customer who was in the store. I would have probably bought some tobacco products had they asked if I need anything else. Not very good customer service. Thanks and have a nice day.

resp.text: We apologize for the experience you described. We can assure you that behavior goes against our culture standards. We have alerted the Operational Leader over that location to take swift action.

name: Orlando Crawford
text:
Up to the other day I was a faithful customer. I Love the dark roasted coffee. I go there every morning & on both of my off days. Service is friendly. I get a large coffee & reuse the cup the next morning so I can get it  @ $.99. Instead of the $1.07. The special is refills are just $.99. There cup or your own. I haven't missed a day in six month. Just ask my wife. I always give the $.03 to the charity or just say to the cashier to keep it tell I'm in a bind or the next person needs it.  For Trusting right. Well on the morning I only had exactly $.97 cents but no cup. I got told I would be charged $1.07. Ok, I come s7 days a week, I buy gas twice a month, I fuel up, $35- 45 dollars biweekly. I have two car so I fuel them both. For $.08 cents you would lose a good customer. That spends over $250.00+ a month. You do the math. Yea your sales are good, you are one of the busiest store in Huntsville, and your coffee sale drive your business. But you lost a good and faithful customer this week. Sad I can't get my favorite coffee any longer from you but in the long run you will loss more. Sorry & I'll keep my &.08 cents and donate it to a worthy charity.
Best wishes

name: Brian East
text: The staff in this place around 10:15 p.m. on Wednesday 11.1.17 were ghetto an incompetent. I don't live in Huntsville and never come to this side of town, but tonight I gave a coworker a ride home and decided to stop by and get gas and a can of chewing tobacco.  My coworker offered to go in and pay for the gas so I asked him to grab a can of dip.  He came back out and I realized they gave him the wrong can. He went back in and asked them to switch it , and they wouldn't. I decided I would go in and politely ask them to make it right, as I walked in the cashier and a group of black girls were looking at me and saying " Y'all don't go nowhere white boy mad , they gone be blood ". I politely asked the other cashier to switch my dip and he explained that the "laws for Mapco " stated that he could not exchange it once it left the door. I just politely asked if Mapco laws were different than those in the rest of Alabama. Once I realized he was not going to make it right I left the can on the counter and told them to keep it. I'm sure they pocketed my $3. People like the employees I encountered tonight are the ones that give certain parts of Huntsville a bad name. I won't be back. ~Brian from Athens.

resp.text:
Brian I assure you this is not the MAPCO culture and will be addressed. I would like to speak with you further about this incident. Can you please email me your contact information? guestexperience@mapcoexpress.com

text:
The sandwiches and tenders were good.  The cashier was nice.  The new promo sweet potato waffle fries tasted good but were cold. Offer for Sundays... kids receive free kids meal with adult combo.  We ordered two adult combos and one child's meal.  After we sat down, I noticed that they didn't honor their own special and charged me for the kids meal.

The kids meal included bottled water as a choice. I had to ask for the bottled water because they were preparing us tap water.  The kids meal side choice of applesauce was rung up correctly, but they gave us curly fries.  We ordered a Dr. Pepper for one adult drink, and it was rung up correctly.  They gave us water instead.  They did refund me $3 cash for the $2.99 kids meal.  I guess I donated the 27 or 30 cents tax.  Not sure.

name: Michele Upton
text: I'm not sure what the problem currently is with the roast beef but the last few times I've ordered the beef and cheddar it's been a thick, miscut mess! Once it was just a roast beef (no cheddar) but still a horrible cut of meat that I had to throw away. The texture was rough and unpalatable. My order tonight was also thick and nowhere near the pleasant thin roast beef that I expect to get from Arby's. I'm at the point of not going to Arby's again because I'm tired of wasting my money on a less than eatable product. My husband has already washed his hands of them because of wrong orders at the drive thru. Who wants to drive all the way back to the restaurant to complain when you're already at home and tired? I don't and of course restaurants know this! Doubt seriously if I'll be back any time soon! Or maybe ever!

name: David Cagle
text:
As always, the food and service as well as the workers were great.  The workers were attentive and friendly as well as knowledgeable.  I've heard a lot of bad things about this Arby's, but even though there are times that that workers are possibly not "wonderful", I dare say that people who write bad reviews likely have more "bad" days than most others. That's why they have nothing positive to say about people who are new to the job,  having problems of their own or don't like the job they're having to do because they can't get the job they want or are qualified for.
Then you have those who just totally enjoy berating others and the business they go to.  They're angry because all they could get was a roast beef sandwich when they wanted a ribeye steak or maybe a T Bone.  I'm sorry you're stuck in a place where you aren't happy with your lowly position and can't afford to go to Ruth's Chris Steakhouse or even get a sirloin or T Bone from Waffle House.  Get over it.  Work hard wherever you are and do the best job anyone has ever done and that will help you get a chance for a position you can work up to. And stop complaining about others. Try being positive for a change and see what a difference it makes in your life and your career.
I will definitely be going back to ARBY'S to eat.  And,  by the way, no  I don't have any affiliation with the company or any of the employees.

name: Mary Brand
text:
This is a clean store with a variety of every food you desire. The best place to do a western union transaction, it's completely paperless now.
I love the fact that they have scooters as I often need one due to my disability. Their employees have always been helpful and friendly anytime I visit. Their in store pharmacy is a plus , and saves time without having to go to a bigger "mart" store crowded with people.

name: Jon Bongiovanni
text:
The manager is an extremely nice gentleman and a very  charitable one as well. My concern is with the produce section. I cook almost every night and we like to have somewhat fresh produce. I’ve complained numerous times to the staff about flies and other bugs in the produce area and nothing seems to be done about it. The produce is also typically old and starting to turn. The ladies in the deli are always delightful and other than the produce section I would say that it’s a decent grocery store

It does concern me that the Google review shows great produce because this has not been the case for years.

name: Lisa Lyons
text: One of my favorite grocery stores because I always come out having saved an unexpected amount of money! Great store brands on different items but if you insist on going with name brand, they have those, too. There always seems to be some sort of sale on their beef, pork or seafood. Lots of BOGO's. Ads change every week plus they have an app for your phone that lets you see that week's ad. Can't beat that!

name: Chris Hanes
text:
Winn Dixie is not exactly known for its cleanliness but this store ranks up there with any Publix or other fancy grocery store in terms of being clean, well-lit and staffed by friendly folks.

There is a Public right down the road but I often find myself here instead when visiting town as the prices are great and the staff is friendly. Sometimes during the later hours, things aren't quite as great, thus the 4 star review instead of a 5 star review.

Also, sometimes on Friday nights they have the smoker going out front and music is playing and it's a party at the local WD and it doesn't get much better than that.

name: Jason Yeager (Jason)
text: Good store to shop, but there have been too many times that I have visited and left without the items I went to get. It seems they have difficulty keeping stock of sale items. Deli food items are often gone before mid-afternoon so don't go searching for a fully cooked rack of ribs or rotisserie chicken for dinner after 1:00 or so. They also mislabel fish in the seafood market. I have seen them selling the lane snapper species labeled as the higher quality, better tasting and more expensive red snapper. This is a federal law violation so they might want to be careful what they call their fish. They usually have a decent selection of meats,  but they often have an attitude if something is not out there and you ask them to get you the item.

name: Scotty Weeks
text: The atmosphere is amazing, with paintings on the walls that were painted by the owner. The Fast & Fit meals are delicious and very well priced. The pizzas are made to order and will rival any pizza place around in taste and price. They have several craft beers on tap and bottle beer also if you don't want to experiment with craft beer. The service is great. You do have to go up to the counter or bar and place your own order, plus fix your own drinks, but the food is well worth it. I've been to Eddie's several times and plan to go back very soon.

name: Tim Champlin
text: I love this bar. Great food. Great staff. Best hamburger in town. Huge pretzel lots of tapps, best bourbon and scotch selection in North Alabama. Great atmosphere, I just love being here.

name: Brian
text: The atmosphere is awesome! It's completely not "Decatur" which is exactly what we need. The food is consistently amazing the service is fantastic. After several visits, this has been a legit 5 star experience to-date.

name: Klaudia Thomas
text: Great experience and amazing food. The new bar, cool modern atmosphere paired with quality service and delicious food makes this place one of the best in Decatur. We will definitely be back.

name: Amber Stout
text: I am not sure what a Gastro Pub is and I don't think the people who run the place do either. It was a confusing mess. You order at the bar which is not set up for ordering. Then if you want just a soda or water you have to go to the other side, then search for a cup. Then they have like two menus you have to look at in the ordering area. The food was okay at best. Overall, it was confusing and frustrating experience. We will not be back.

name: Carson Elmore
text: The food was fine, if a little skimpy for the price, and having to go to the bar to order, even during dinner, was a little strange. Your best bet is one of their fit meals.

name: Darin Burnham
text: I made arrangements for a surprise party for my wife's birthday. The owners Svetlana and Tim Champlin went above and beyond to make this party a huge success. My wife and I do not eat any type of sugar so Svetlana made her a ketone-style cake that was amazing! They even played "They Say it's Your Birthday" as we walked into the restaurant! You just don't get this kind of treatment anywhere else! We recommend trying them out for any of your upcoming events or just a night out.

name: John Castle
text: Wish I could give them 10 stars. Stopped in for dinner with some friends,they have a true clean food menu for the ones on their summer diets. Me I get the triple threat hamburger and thick cut fries, or the peminto bacon sandwich and a Frito pie with the best chili sauce this side of Cincinnati's skyline chili. The dinner music tonight was incredible, they had Monty Holmes that wrote troubador for George Straight and he sang it, fantastic. These guys are killing it in every way, food music, staff. I got to meet the owner tonight she was super nice and perfesional, and very attentive to everyone in the place and it was packed. She runs a tight ship. You do have to go to the bar to order which can be a hastle but they are quick and it beats waiting on a waitress.
